Package commands.util

Class CommandObject

java.lang.Object
commands.util.CommandObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
Ban, Help, Kick, Lines, Shutdown, Silence, Unban
public abstract class CommandObject
extends java.lang.Object
Description:
Abstract class that all commands are an extension of. Contains all descriptor methods used in describing every command. Initializes all the commands through the init method. Any "helper" methods related to commands are contained here as well, such as the devMessage method, compare method, etc.

Date: August 24, 2021

Since:
1.0.0
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Harrison Hoggard

    • execute

      public abstract void execute​(net.dv8tion.jda.api.entities.Guild guild, net.dv8tion.jda.api.entities.Member member, net.dv8tion.jda.api.entities.TextChannel textChannel, java.lang.String[] arg)
      Description:
      Abstract method to execute the command.
      Parameters:
      guild - the guild that the command was executed from
      member - the member that gave the command request
      textChannel - the text channel that the command was requested from
      arg - the command itself split into separate words. This allows any other arguments to be derived for specialized use
      Since:
      1.0.0

    • init

      public static void init()
      Description:
      NEW COMMANDS ARE ADDED HERE Adds all the commands to the static "commands" array. Once all commands have been added, the getTypes method is called to initalize the command categories.
      Since:
      1.0.0

    • getTypes

      public static void getTypes()
      Description:
      Traverses through the commands and retrieves their categories. These categories are then placed in the static "types" array to be used later in the "Help" command.
      Since:
      1.0.0

    • compare

      public boolean compare​(java.lang.String cmd)
      Description:
      Compares the member's requested command name to the names of the stored commands.
      Parameters:
      cmd - the inputed name of the command the user wants to execute.
      Returns:
      true if the user input matches the name of a stored command
      false if the user input does not match the stored command's name
      Since:
      1.0.0

    • hasAdminRole

      public boolean hasAdminRole​(net.dv8tion.jda.api.entities.Member member)
      Description:
      Determines if the member requesting a command has permission to execute the command.
      Parameters:
      member - member that requested a command's execution
      Returns:
      true if either the command requires admin privileges and the user has them, or the command doesn't require admin privileges
      false if the command requires admin privileges and the user does not have them
      Since:
      1.0.0

    • isBotOwner

      public boolean isBotOwner​(net.dv8tion.jda.api.entities.Member member)
      Description:
      Determines if the member requesting a command has permission to execute an owner-only command.
      Parameters:
      member - member that requested a command's execution
      Returns:
      true if either the command requires owner privileges and the member ID is present in the private.json file, or the command doesn't require them
      false if the command requires owner privileges and the user does not have their ID as the bot host
      Since:
      1.0.0
